template.name: mat-dialog:?
template.value:
<!--

dialog sample code in ts
---

1. Get reference to dialog
constructor(public dialog: MatDialog) {
}

2. Open the dialog like this

this.dialogRef = this.dialog.open(CustomDialog, this.config);

(or)

this.dialogRef = this.dialog.open(CustomDialog);

(or)

@ViewChild(TemplateRef) template: TemplateRef<any>; // refers to a html <template> element
this.dialogRef = this.dialog.open(this.template, this.config);

sample dialog config
---

config: MatDialogConfig = {
    disableClose: false,
    hasBackdrop: true,
    backdropClass: '',
    width: '',
    height: '',
    position: {
      top: '',
      bottom: '',
      left: '',
      right: ''
    },
    data: {
      message: 'custom message'
    }
  }

Receive data in the dialog
--

export class CustomDialog {
  constructor(
    private dialogRef: MatDialogRef<CustomDialog>,
    @Inject(MAT_DIALOG_DATA) public data: any) { }
}

Send result back to dialog parent from dialog
--

export class CustomDialog {
  constructor(
    private dialogRef: MatDialogRef<CustomDialog>,
    @Inject(MAT_DIALOG_DATA) public data: any) { }

  sendDataToParent() {
    this.dialogRef.close(dataForParent);
  }
}


disable body level scrolling by subscribing to dialog event subscription
---

dialog.afterOpen.subscribe((ref: MatDialogRef<any>) => {
  if (!doc.body.classList.contains('no-scroll')) {
    doc.body.classList.add('no-scroll');
  }
});

dialog.afterAllClosed.subscribe(() => {
  doc.body.classList.remove('no-scroll');
});

-->
